-- Steelcase profit up, international business strong
-- 
-- Thu Mar 29, 2007 10:21am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/29/us-steelcase-results-idUSN2941962720070329

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Steelcase Inc. ( SCS.N ), the world's biggest office furniture maker, said on Thursday quarterly earnings tripled, helped by growth in its international business. 

 Fourth-quarter net income rose to $29.3 million, or 20 cents a share, from $9.3 million, or 6 cents a share, a year ago. Revenue rose 5.4 percent to $779 million. The Grand Rapids, Michigan-based company said it expects first-quarter earnings of 15 cents to 20 cents per share including special items. The company sees first-quarter revenue up 6 percent to 10 percent.